To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 287,062.51
- Total Revenue = 791,992.51

Now, plug in the numbers:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{287,062.51}{791,992.51} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 0.3624 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 36.24\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '36.24%'} }
```
